content:
This photograph is part of the "Shooting for the Gold" Olympic series by Walter Iooss Jr. The exclusive 10 edition mint run was airdropped randomly as a surprise thank you to 10 of Immutable Image's first collectors.

"When we took off in the helicopter for the sailing competitions in Caracas, it was a beautiful sunny day. But by the time we reached the site, a huge cloud had rolled over the boats. We started to go back, but then tried one more pass. The sun came out for about five minutes and this photograph was the result."
 
Fujichrome 50, 85mm lens.

Walter Iooss, Jr.
New York City
September 1, 1984
title: Yachting, Caracas Venezuela 1983

content:
“Michael Jordan, 1984 Olympics” by Walter Iooss Jr. is the first NFT of Immutable Image and Iooss’ first NFT on the Solana blockchain.

In the artist’s own words: 

“This was the first time I ever saw and photographed Michael Jordan, and an image that I forgot existed until only recently. At this Gold Medal game, I could begin to see his incredible ability to play and his charismatic personality shine. At that point, no one could have imagined that he would become the star and legend that he has become. 

It would be three years from when I took this that I first met Michael, and we began our wonderful working relationship. Going through my archive for this NFT exhibition resurfaced this fantastic image. So it only feels right to honor this moment in time, the first-ever photograph minted on Immutable Image, with my first-ever photograph of Michael.”  

Walter Iooss Jr. 
September 29, 2021

content: Isseu & Fatima, from Wayne Lawrence's first monograph, Orchard Beach: The Bronx Riviera. Made over a seven-year period, this collection of engaging and iconic portraits celebrates the diversity and community of one of New York City's most popular beaches which made its way to print as an award-winning book. Lawrence's subjects are a community standing in defiance of popular opinion, proud to call Orchard Beach their own. This is the genesis NFT mint for Mr. Lawrence.
title: Isseu & Fatima, 2007

content:
The Notorious B.I.G. standing in front of a building on St. James Place in Brooklyn, NY, 1994.
This image is part of Gonzalez's historical Polaroid series capturing The Notorious B.I.G. in the early days of his career. When Gonzalez captured this image outside of Biggie’s mother’s Brooklyn apartment in 1994, he was still relatively unknown. In the immediate days after this session, he released his first album, Ready to Die, and the rest is history.
This is the genesis NFT mint for Ms. Gonzalez.
title: The Notorious B.I.G. #9

content:
"I've always wanted to take this shot but couldn't because of restrictions on the photographer positions at actual competitions. I photographed the runner with an 800mm lens at f/16 for good depth of field and kept them on the starting line for at least half an hour until their arms began to quiver." 

Walter Iooss, Jr.
September 1, 1984
title: Runners On Their Mark, 1983
